A: You can use the JSONObject.keys() method to get an iterator over the keys in the JSONObject. Then, you can use the get() method to get the value associated with each key.
Here is an example:
JSONObject jsonObject = new JSONObject("{\"key1\":\"a\",\"key2\":\"b\",\"key3\":\"c\",\"key4\":\"d\"}");
Iterator<String> keys = jsonObject.keys();
while(keys.hasNext()) {
    String key = keys.next();
    String value = jsonObject.getString(key);
    System.out.println(key + value);
}

